# Salesforce Metadata Deploy Gotchas

A high-signal list of deploy failures that recur across Salesforce metadata projects. These are framework-level (not project-specific) and safe to reuse anywhere.

- **Permission sets: do NOT include `fieldPermissions` for required fields** ‚Äî Salesforce rejects FLS on required fields. Omit required fields from the permissionset XML.
- **Master-Detail fields: omit `<required>true</required>`** ‚Äî MD fields are always required by definition; including the tag fails the deploy.
- **Required lookup + `deleteConstraint: SetNull` is invalid** ‚Äî use `Restrict` or `CascadeDelete` when a Lookup field is required.
- **`<enableActivities>` is required in the CustomObject XSD** ‚Äî must be present (even `false`) before `<enableHistory>`, or the XSD validator rejects it.
- **Roll-up summary fields must deploy AFTER the child object** ‚Äî deploy the roll-up in a separate pass once the child object is live.
- **Url field type max is 255 chars** ‚Äî regardless of any longer value mentioned in a field description. Don't seed/test with longer URLs.
- **Restricted picklists reject unlisted values** ‚Äî seed/test data must use only the declared values.
- **CLT / `@apexClassType` "Unsupported Data Type" warning in *Map to Variable*** ‚Äî cosmetic; safe to ignore (see CLT best-practices guide).
- **CLT `schema.json` MUST use the `c__` prefix on `@apexClassType/c__Type`** ‚Äî the unprefixed form deploys cleanly but breaks `sf agent preview --use-live-actions` (HTTP 400) and the LightningType becomes **immutable** once an active BotVersion references it. Get it right on first deploy.
- **CLT `renderer.json` allows only `definition`** ‚Äî adding an `attributes` block fails deploy with `unevaluatedProperties`.
- **Re-publish the Embedded Service Deployment after publishing a CLT** ‚Äî otherwise the card won't render in the ECv2 widget even though deploy succeeded.
- **Compound Address sub-fields cannot be written via `JSON.deserialize` into an SObject** ‚Äî the platform rejects compound sub-field writes through deserialized SObjects. Assign `Location__City__s` / `Location__StateCode__s` / `Location__CountryCode__s` manually after deserialize, passed as separate params.
- **Address State/Country picklists reject free-text** ‚Äî when State/Country Picklists are enabled, sub-fields expect ISO codes (`US`, `KE`, `VA`), not labels (`Kenya`). Use `lightning-combobox` sourced from `getDescribe().getPicklistValues()`, not `lightning-input type="text"`.
- **Static-resource deploys can silently fail in some orgs** ‚Äî if `sf project deploy` fails on a static resource, STOP and flag it; do not work around silently. Manual fallback: Setup ‚Üí Static Resources ‚Üí New.
- **`LightningConfirm` is unreliable in LWR (Experience Cloud) sites** ‚Äî use a custom `lightning-modal` child for delete confirmations instead.
- **`lightning-notice` is not reliably available in LWR sites** ‚Äî render alert banners with a custom SLDS `div` + `lightning-icon` instead.
- **LWR components should target `lightningCommunity__Page` / `lightningCommunity__Default` only** ‚Äî do not add `lightning__RecordPage` / `lightning__AppPage` targets for Experience-Cloud-only components.
- **Deploy by explicit named component, never by folder** ‚Äî a broad folder deploy (e.g. `objects/Case/fields`) fails when *any* unrelated field in that folder has values that don't match the target org. Use `--metadata "CustomField:Case.My_Field__c"`, one flag per component.
- **`GenAiPlugin` (Agentforce subagent/topic) `sortOrder` is normalised to `0` by the org** ‚Äî do not retrieve-to-verify; a retrieve only rewrites `sortOrder` and marks the file `Changed`. Trust the deploy output table (`State: Created`/`Changed`). Use lexicographically ordered `developerName` values (`..._01`‚Ä¶`_06`) so Builder shows steps in order; the repo XML is the source of truth.
- **`GenAiPlanner` may not be retrievable** (`Entity type 'GenAiPlanner' is not available in this api version`) ‚Äî link topics to the agent in legacy Agentforce Builder, not via a `plannerField` element (fails parse in API v66).
- **`GenAiPlugin` is not queryable via Tooling API** (`sObject type 'GenAiPlugin' is not supported`) ‚Äî verify existence via the deploy output table or the Builder Topics tab, not SOQL.
- **Never use unscoped metadata pulls to "explore"** ‚Äî `sf project retrieve start --metadata GenAiPlugin` (no member) or wildcard `GenAiPlannerBundle` retrieves bloat the repo with 200+ unrelated files. Always retrieve **named** components once you know the API name.
- **`--test-level RunSpecifiedTests` silently skips on sandboxes** ‚Äî `‚óØ Running Tests - Skipped` is not a pass. Run `sf apex run test --tests <Class>Test ... --synchronous` separately. On single-class synchronous runs, `Org Wide Coverage 0%` is meaningless ‚Äî trust the per-class row.
- **CLT `schema.json` MUST keep the `c__` prefix on `@apexClassType/c__Type`** ‚Äî omitting it deploys fine but breaks `sf agent preview --use-live-actions` (HTTP 400) and becomes **immutable** once an active BotVersion references the Lightning Type. Get it right the first time.
- **CLT `renderer.json` allows only `definition`** ‚Äî any `attributes` block fails deploy with `unevaluatedProperties`.
- **`sf agent publish authoring-bundle` regenerates the planner bundle from inline `.agent` declarations and strips UI-set fields** ‚Äî including the Output Rendering ‚Üí CLT binding. After setting bindings in Agent Builder UI, deploy `.agent` edits with plain `sf project deploy start --metadata "AiAuthoringBundle:<Name>"` (metadata API) instead, or re-apply the UI bindings immediately after any `agent publish`.
- **Re-publish the Embedded Service Deployment after any CLT/LWC change** ‚Äî Setup ‚Üí Embedded Service Deployments ‚Üí <deployment> ‚Üí Edit ‚Üí Save. Without it the ECv2 site cache serves the old render and the component won't appear in new sessions.
- **CLTs do NOT render in Agent Builder Preview** ‚Äî always smoke-test on the live ECv2 site (incognito) or the Lightning Agentforce panel.
- **Chip-menu / single-object CLTs: ship only `lightningDesktopGenAi/renderer.json`** ‚Äî adding an `enhancedWebChat/renderer.json` override for these breaks deploy with `unevaluatedProperties`; ECv2 falls back to the desktop renderer automatically.

> Add new lines only when a failure recurs and is **framework-level**. Keep project-specific gotchas in your project's architecture rule.

